Problem on Probability-3 - Placement Exercise
NOTE: This kind of question is very common in campus placement ( TCS, Wipro, etc.) 
because it makes the use of probability logics.

Problem:
A dice is thrown once.
What is the probability of getting (a) an even number, (b) a number greater than 4?

Solution: 
Note: Probability = Favourable outcomes Ã· Total outcomes

Total outcomes when a dice is thrown = 6
(Possible numbers: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6)

(a) Even number:
Even numbers = {2, 4, 6} â†’ 3 outcomes
Probability = Favourable outcomes Ã· Total outcomes
Probability = 3 Ã· 6 = 1/2 âœ…

(b) Number greater than 4:
Numbers greater than 4 = {5, 6} â†’ 2 outcomes
Probability = Favourable outcomes Ã· Total outcomes
Probability = 2 Ã· 6 = 1/3 âœ…

Final Answer:
ğŸ‘ (a) Probability of even number = 1/2
ğŸ‘ (b) Probability of number greater than 4 = 1/3
